    pearls: ["The Ballard score is most accurate when performed between 12 and 96 hours of age; earlier assessments may underestimate gestational age due to initial hypotonia", "Neuromuscular maturity assessment is less reliable in ill or sedated neonates", "Physical maturity criteria are less affected by illness and provide more consistent results than neuromuscular criteria in sick neonates"],
